Requires:         R-stats 
Requires:         R-utils 

%description
Draws systematic samples from a population that follows linear trend. The
function returns a matrix comprising of the required samples as its column
vectors. The samples produced are highly efficient and the inter sampling
variance is minimum. The scheme will be useful in various field like
Bioinformatics where the samples are expensive and must be precise in
reflecting the population by possessing least sampling variance.

